news_header: A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket re-entered Earth's atmosphere, causing debris to fall in Poland and possibly Ukraine.
news_original_title: SpaceX rocket debris crashes into Poland
news_text: On February 19, 2025, a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket re-entered Earth's atmosphere uncontrollably, leading to debris falling in Poland and potentially Ukraine. Witnesses reported seeing a fiery object in the sky. Fortunately, no injuries were reported, but experts warn that such uncontrolled re-entries are becoming more common.
